OL,3,CGovernment's energy support schemes
OL,4,C'undoubtedly successful' ` NAO
OL,6,FThe support cost #44 billion ` two-
OL,7,Fthirds lower than the original
OL,8,Festimate of #139 billion, in part
OL,9,Fthanks to lower-than-expected
OL,10,Fwholesale energy prices and a warmer-
OL,11,Fthan-average winter in 2022, the NAO's
OL,12,Freport said.
OL,14,FThe Department for Energy Security and
OL,15,FNet Zero (DESNZ) reported that the
OL,16,Fschemes successfully prevented around
OL,17,F289,000 households in England from
OL,18,Fgoing into fuel poverty while fewer
OL,19,Fpeople chose to disconnect or ration
OL,20,Ftheir energy use, the NAO found.
