OL,3,CGovernment's energy support schemes
OL,4,C'undoubtedly successful' ` NAO
OL,6,FThe schemes suffered a comparatively
OL,7,Flow rate of fraud and error, which
OL,8,FDESNZ estimated at 0.7% of payments `
OL,9,Fworth #291.8 million of the
OL,10,Fprogramme's total expenditure.
OL,12,FThe NAO found that the government's
OL,13,Funderstanding of energy use among the
OL,14,Fcommercial sector was "poor" during
OL,15,Fimplementation of the schemes, which
OL,16,Fled to identical support for all
OL,17,Fbusinesses despite differences in
OL,18,Ftheir energy consumption compared with
OL,19,Fdomestic households.
