OL,6,F"This work is at an early stage of
OL,7,Fdevelopment and it is not clear how
OL,8,FDESNZ will respond in reality."
OL,10,FGeoffrey Clifton-Brown, chairman of
OL,11,Fthe Committee of Public Accounts,
OL,12,Fsaid: "The government's rollout of #44
OL,13,Fbillion of support during the energy
OL,14,Fcrisis succeeded in shielding many
OL,15,Fhouseholds from hardship and keeping
OL,16,Fbusinesses open.
OL,18,F"DESNZ should be commended for its
OL,19,Fquick responses and for its efforts to
OL,20,Fprevent fraud and error in the schemes.
